
REPRESENTATIONAL STATE TRANSFER

It is platform independent , should follow standard protocols

URI - Uniform Resource Identifier

GET -- Get response from specified URI

POST -- Creates a new resource at specified URI

PUT -- Creates or replaces the resource at specified URI

DELETE -- Removes resource at specified URI

PATCH -- Performs partial Update of a resource

Naming Convention::

/users/{id} -- used
getUsers -- not prefered

--> use lower cases

Resource -- It is the primary data representation





 

